    "body": "@avik-pal let me know if this would work or if I misunderstood sharding. \r\nFor the `LatitudeLongitudeGrid` the idea is to have a grid that is similar to the serial grid but shards the underlying metrics. Note that the metrics can have different dimensionalities based on the stretching of the grid.\r\n\r\nWe also need an extension of the distributed-specific methods for sharding. I have added them in this PR (for example, `partition` and `construct_global_array`). \r\nIf I understand correctly, all the partitioning and reconstruction should be handled by sharding, so all these methods for a `Distributed{<:ReactantState}` architecture fall back to the serial methods (which basically do nothing)",
